Comment: Respectively: to finish (eating); to finish something; to finish doing something; to finish something.

Refers especially to movement of the feet. Also niteʔ owxoc̷aχ, 'not quick'; and niteʔ iyaχ 'not quick'.
Includes the idea of movement of the feet. Also -(wo)nowxoc̷inix, 'swift', as in weaving, working, eating, talking, etc. To run fast is iyaχ.
Means 'to dawn' 14.430; lit. 'gray toward below'. leefˀe means 'gray'. To leave early is -(we)kiyaf; to arrive early is -tekiyaf.
Means the last one (to go). Also ewiɬ-i-ix, 'last time'.
Respectively: to go in front/ to go first; only once, cf. 13.010.
Respectively: to go in front/ to go first; only once, cf. 13.010.
Means 'there is nothing (in the interior)'. Cf. 10.491.
Means 'many people', lit. 'many men and women'.
Refers to countable items. ḳi refers to non-countable items, 12.550.
Means 'all the toes (04.380) of the feet'.
Also week in-yaksi-i ḳa ewiɬ in-fˀiʔ ikets, means 'all fingers and one foot' 04.370.
Means 'all our (inclusive) fingers (04.340) of the hand'.
Respectively: edge, shore, see 01.270; opposite edge.
Respectively: edge, shore, see 01.270; opposite edge.
Means to close the door. -itˀixem ḳap means to close the mouth.
Means to open the door. -itˀix kˀax means to open the mouth. To open a flower is kˀufxem neʔ ɬʔopˀom.
Means to divide in half; cf. 12.230. To divide in various pieces is -akˀesaxxuʔ.
Intrans., cf. 'high' 12.310; 'top' 12.330. Also -xi-pham 'to be above something'.
Means to be at the chest (04.400) of one. To go first (before) on the trail is -oxoʔ, intrans. To go before another is -oxo-o-kˀoy. 'Primogeniture' is -oxofikˀi.
The latter also means 'near'. Also ha-n-i-xup, 'I am beside someone'.
The latter also means 'near'. Also ha-n-i-xup, 'I am beside someone'.
Lit. means to be at the back (04.190) of one. Also, intrans. -tekelen-xuʔ; 'behind something' -tekelen-i-xup-xu; 'behind something (while in movement)'.
Respectively: to injure someone; to injure various.
Respectively: to injure someone; to injure various.
Respectively: cuidar algo/a alguien; vigilar algo.
Respectively: cuidar algo/a alguien; vigilar algo.
Means to put on the center of the head for carrying.
The latter means 'enter a house'. To enter inside/ the interior (penetrate) is wi-xi-texem; to enter a river is wi-xi-xuʔ.
The latter means 'enter a house'. To enter inside/ the interior (penetrate) is wi-xi-texem; to enter a river is wi-xi-xuʔ.
Fro example, climb a tree. Also -weɬ-i-ki-pham 'climb a ladder'; -ik-i-ki-pham 'climb a hill'. Cf. 'rise' 10.210.
Intransitive form. The paradigm contains: hak; ɬak; ik; xuuk. The vowel /a/ occurs in desiderative and causative.
Means to lift a heavy object from the floor. Also -(e)kumetsxu to lift a light-weight object from the floor.
The latter means to rise, after being seated or lying down.
The latter means to rise, after being seated or lying down.
Refers to fanning a person; -xikaf-in-xem refers to fanning a fire.

Respectively: bolsa de arpillera; b. de caraguatá. Also -kekiʔ (f.), b. de cuero de ñandú; -ɬuk (m.), b. de red para llevar el cántaro; tanxeptileʔ (f.), b. antigua; moc̷ʔoc̷kiʔ (f.), b. que se ata a la cintura.

Respectively: bolsa de arpillera; b. de caraguatá. Also -kekiʔ (f.), b. de cuero de ñandú; -ɬuk (m.), b. de red para llevar el cántaro; tanxeptileʔ (f.), b. antigua; moc̷ʔoc̷kiʔ (f.), b. que se ata a la cintura.
Means 'coin' 11.440; 'metal' or article of metal, such as a can, money, etc.
Also means 'bathe' 04.690. lixuʔ means to 'clean'. To 'wash the face' is -(wa)tunaχ tapulix (intrans.); -wanḳa (intrans.) 'wash the hands'.
Respectively: pour, spill; empty (a container). Cf. 'disappear' 10.491.
Respectively: pour, spill; empty (a container). Cf. 'disappear' 10.491.
Refers to squeezing out liquid; cf. previous entry.
Refers to pressing, without liquid or juice; see next entry.
E. g. hosxaʔ neʔ ɬʔax means to rub a hide (skin) to make it soft.
To tear something fragile. -iwxafʔitikˀi is to tear cloth.
Means to cut in two pieces.
Means to cut in pieces. Also -anapkˀasitxuʔ.
Such as to fold paper. -itˀix ḳˀul ḳˀul is to bend the body.
Such as to bend a stick.
Latter form refers to a trunk without branches.
Latter form refers to a trunk without branches.
Means an instrument to clean; also means 'broom' 09.380.
A place without trees. -wenḳˀen-hewet (m.) means place that is planted.
Means one who lives in the rural area.
A comb made from the thorns of the 'carandá'.
Neologism, used for the nose. Lit. 'for mucus' 04.232.
Means to make marks on the face with the juice of witwextutiʔ (f.), a large tree (Genipapo) or (ñandipá).
Respectively: cinta de mujeres para el cuello; cinta de hombres para sujetarse el cabello.
Respectively: cinta de mujeres para el cuello; cinta de hombres para sujetarse el cabello.
Respectively: open shoe (sandal) 'ojota, abarca'; zapato de cuero grueso con cordones.
Respectively: open shoe (sandal) 'ojota, abarca'; zapato de cuero grueso con cordones.
Man's clothing; a garment made of feathers, used during the fiestas. Cf. 'spin' 06.310; 'sew' 06.350.
Refers to the ancient clothing of the women.
Can be expressed as -ukin-ets-xuʔ naʔpenyiloʔ kaʔ woteniɬ, means to add color to the cloth.
Intransitive. Transitive form is -tii ~ ɬii. Also cf. 09.750.
'Drink' is -iya-. 'Corn drink' is naac̷ˀaxkinak (m.); 'manioc drink' is c̷ipunak (m.).
Refers to a wild pepper, Capsicum chacoense.
Respectively: poroto de monte (Capparis retusa); fruto del poroto de monte; poroto americano (Phaseolus vulgaris o Vigna unguiculata).
Respectively: poroto de monte (Capparis retusa); fruto del poroto de monte; poroto americano (Phaseolus vulgaris o Vigna unguiculata).

Respectively: p. for eating; p. for drinking chicha.

Respectively: food that cannot be eaten raw; any food.
Refers to 'mono caraya'. Also kˀateni (f.), 'monito cají'.
Refers to Dusicyon gymnocercus. Also c̷ˀiyaḳ (f.), Cerdocyonthous.
Refers to 'paloma montaraz'. Also ofotaχ (m.), 'paloma doméstica'.
Refers to white heron, Egretta alba. Other forms are wanhewut (m.), 'garza mora (Ardea cocoi)'; waʔ (m.), 'garza pico de pato (Cochlearius cochlearius)'; ɬoxopo (m.), 'garcita (Egretta thula)'.
Refers to wild duck, such as Cairina moschata.
Refers to Tayassu albirostris. Other forms are c̷afinheʔ (f.), 'Dicotyles tajacu'; and timkenaχ (m.), 'Catagonus wagneri'.
Other forms indicate the distance between speakers.
Fem. form is ilpekiʔ; 'my cousin (fem.)' is pekiʔ.
-eneɬetxiʔ is to cool something, as the coolness of the shade.
'Lucero', the morning star is neɬu-wokiʔ; cf. 'day' 14.410. The 'evening star' is xukaχewokiʔ; cf. 'night' 14.420.
A tree which has not been planted by someone. naxkak-et is a bunch of trees. Cf. 'mountain range' 01.220.
Respectively: pozo; agua estancada en el monte; pozo cavado por el hombre (< 'cavar').

A flowing stream is xey naʔ haḳḳiʔ.
Also means 'beak' 04.241, refers to 'point' 12.352. -pas is 'lip' 04.250. See also 'nipple' 04.412.
Means a deep lagoon. kaɬiʔ (f.) is a shallow lagoon.
Means the growing river; cf. 01.322. An overflowing river is tˀixay-pham naʔ haḳḳiʔ.
Also keɬey kutek, 'quebracho colorado'; means when autumn arrives, the quebracho colorado is flowering.
Also means 'dance' 10.440. 'To have a good time' is -awitxiʔ.
Refers to physical pain. Also aʔtaχ (m.).
Respectively: preocupado; ansioso por hacer algo.

Masc. form. Fem. form is ekun-heʔ.
Means not to be sure. Cf. 17.180.
For example, pan ɬa-n-i, lit. '(interrogative) 2nd verbal-locative', 'where is it'.

Refers to a horn made from a cow (waka) horn.

Fem. is -(i)c̷etife-kiʔ. Means from the same 'village' 19.160.
Means a non-Indian stranger. Fem. form is sonto-kiʔ (f.).
